<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idca390b36-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598" identifier="/us/usc/t43/s1471h"><num value="1471h">§ 1471h.</num><heading> Availability of appropriations for uniforms or allowances</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Appropriations available to the Department of the Interior for salaries and expenses shall on and after <date date="2004-12-08">December 8, 2004</date>, be available for uniforms or allowances therefor, as authorized by law (<ref href="/us/usc/t5/s5901–590">5 U.S.C. 5901–590</ref>2 and D.C. Code 4–204).</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idca390b37-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598">(<ref href="/us/pl/108/447/dE/tI/s105">Pub. L. 108–447, div. E, title I, § 105</ref>, <date date="2004-12-08">Dec. 8, 2004</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/118/3063">118 Stat. 3063</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
